*******************************************
PYLIB
DESCRIPTION: A collection of Python functions
    for data analysis. Programs are written
    in Python3.

AUTHOR:  Christopher D. Holmes
CONTACT: cdholmes@fsu.edu
*******************************************

CONTENTS:
boxcar.py        - Boxcar (running mean) filters
boxcarpoly.py
gctools.py       - Functions to retrieve properties of GEOS-Chem grids
nctools.py       - High-level functions for reading and writing netCDF files
smafit.py        - Standard Major Axis (SMA) line fitting, including robust methods and error analysis
time_tools.py    - Functions for calculating with dates. e.g. converting dates to fractional years
wstats.py        - Weighted statistics. e.g. weighted mean, weighted R2, etc.
